icProfile?language=EN>Nobbil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Knight<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#330000>(5/30/02 9:56:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=590.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ITR enforced on Legends!</span><hr size=1> Township Rebellion has been dominating the server.  So those of us who CHOSE not be take part in the life of being in a "Uber Raiding Guild" are getting walked over by TR.  This system is a way of helping ensure smaller guilds get a fair shot at the spawns that they are capable of doing and not get walked over by a larger guilds.   <br>
<br>
Each guild gets a Trial and a fair opportunity to prove themselves and get themselves ranked.  TR still will have practically no threat in the upper tiers.  My guild at best may be a Tier 3 and we know it and accept it.  We chose to be a friends and honor based guild first and foremost.  So, what do the smart guilds do?  They set up a plan and prepare for their Trial and get into the system.  As they grow in power or size (if they chose to), they can move up the Tiers.<br>
<br>
There is no guarantee your reserved mob will even spawn.  If it doesn't or you don't kill it, Sat night it goes free for all.  <br>
<br>
A few of my guildies and friends come from servers where ITR has been successful.  Some done by the server population themselves or in some cases done in conjunction with the GM's.  ITR can work if it's done right.  <br>
<br>
Here is something that the SH system will stop:  I can remember a time when I was in LOTD and we had fought all the way down to The THO and were minutes away from engaging and Afterlife came in the back way and killed it.  I'm sorry, but that is extremely fooked up.  Hey Tallas, do you remember that night?  I sure do, I was there too.  I'd worked down with the guild from the entrance.  We all were extremely pissed.  We had sufficient force to kill it.  We had fought all the way down. If you were there, think about how YOU felt at that moment that AL walked over us.  This system prevents that from happening.  If you still fail to kill the mob, it goes free-for all, then it's a race that the uber guilds will win.<br>
<br>
<br>
The SH system will prevent that BS from happening.  My guild on Legends was leap frogged in SSRA by TR as we were fighting down to Rhags.  That's BS.  Anyone in a smaller guild that has been victimized by stuff like that can relate.<br>
<br>
Tallas, how bout getting a clue before you throw out such ignorant statements?   There may come a day that ITR and reservation systems become the norm.  What are you going to do then, when you can no longer bully and walk over other guilds?  Every GM I've ever chatted with just hates to get caught in the middle of this type of dispute where people get screwed over.<br>
<br>
Tallas you so bad mouth Legends,  which you don't even play on .  You know nothing about the community established there.  You bad mouth this ITR system.  You have been screwed over plenty of times I'm sure in your EQ career.  You may also have taken pleasure in screwing others over.  Think about all the times you or your guild got walked over by a larger guild and remember how you felt.  I'll guaran-dam-tee you that you wished for an ITR system at that moment.  I've personally seen you whine and cry like a baby over things not going your way.<br>
<br>
